data.oai_dc:dc: Microsoft Excel spreadsheet containing raw coordinate data of labellum landmarks for the Corallorhiza striata complex In the first row are labels of each landmark (each appears twice, next each other). The row below these are the the X and Y-coordinate labels corresponding to each landmark (e.g. X2, Y2). Data represent positions (i.e. coordinates) on a pixel grid, and are not standard units of measurement. Row labels are voucher numbers for individuals. Data were colleced by Craig Barrett [cfb66@cornell.edu].
